#Checking for missing values and duplicate rows
def checking_for_missingVals_and_duplicates():
    # Check for missing values in the dataset
    missing_values = data.isnull().sum()
    print("Missing values in the dataset: ",missing_values)
    # Check for duplicate rows in the dataset
    duplicate_rows = data.duplicated().sum()
    print("No. of duplicate rows in the dataset: ",duplicate_rows)
checking_for_missingVals_and_duplicates()

#Yearly Trend of Hate crimes

# Group data by year and count the number of incidents per year
yearly_trends = data.groupby('Complaint Year Number').size()

# Use a seaborn palette
palette = sns.color_palette("Spectral", len(yearly_trends))

# Plotting the bar graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
yearly_trends.plot(kind='bar', color=palette)
plt.title('Yearly Trend of Hate Crimes')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Hate Crimes')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)

# Show plot
plt.show()

#Monthly Distribution of hate crimes over the years 
# Extract month data for all years
months = data['Month Number']

# Define month names for x-ticks
month_names = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']
palette = sns.color_palette("viridis", 12)

# Plotting the histogram
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
n, bins, patches = plt.hist(months, bins=12, edgecolor='black', rwidth=0.8)

for i in range(12):
    patches[i].set_facecolor(palette[i])

plt.title('Monthly Distribution of Hate Crimes Over the Years')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Number of Hate Crimes')
plt.xticks(range(1, 13), month_names)

# Show plot
plt.show()

#Distribution of hate crimes by Borough

# Filter relevant columns
data_filtered = data[['Patrol Borough Name', 'Complaint Year Number']]

# Define a palette
palette = sns.color_palette("husl", len(data_filtered['Patrol Borough Name'].unique()))

# Plotting box plots
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.boxplot(x='Patrol Borough Name', y='Complaint Year Number', data=data_filtered, palette=palette)
plt.title('Distribution of Hate Crimes by Borough')
plt.xlabel('Borough')
plt.ylabel('Year')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.show()

In [25]:
# Filter data for a specific range of years and precincts
filtered_data = data[(data['Complaint Year Number'] >= 2015) & (data['Complaint Year Number'] <= 2020)]
filtered_data = filtered_data[filtered_data['Complaint Precinct Code'].isin(filtered_data['Complaint Precinct Code'].value_counts().index[:20])]

heatmap_data = filtered_data.pivot_table(index='Complaint Precinct Code', columns='Complaint Year Number', aggfunc='size', fill_value=0)

plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))
sns.heatmap(heatmap_data, cmap="YlGnBu", annot=True, fmt="d")
plt.title('Heat Map of Hate Crimes Across Different Precincts Over the Years')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Precinct Code')
plt.show()

# Scatter Plot: Number of Incidents vs. Number of Arrests
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
data['Arrest Made'] = data['Arrest Date'].notna().astype(int)
yearly_incidents = data.groupby('Complaint Year Number').size()
yearly_arrests = data.groupby('Complaint Year Number')['Arrest Made'].sum()
plt.scatter(yearly_incidents.index, yearly_incidents.values, color='blue', label='Incidents')
plt.scatter(yearly_arrests.index, yearly_arrests.values, color='red', label='Arrests')
plt.plot(yearly_incidents.index, yearly_incidents.values, linestyle='-', color='blue', alpha=0.5)
plt.plot(yearly_arrests.index, yearly_arrests.values, linestyle='-', color='red', alpha=0.5)
plt.title('Scatter Plot of Number of Incidents vs. Number of Arrests Over the Years')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
